# Scheduling & booking (optional)

## Staff logins
- Groomers: https://mobiledog-salon.com/groomer/login (Melanie / Diamond / Jessica)
- Admin: https://mobiledog-salon.com/admin/login

## Environment variables (Vercel production)

Required for persistent appointments on Vercel:
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` ‚Äî from [Upstash Redis](https://upstash.com) (Vercel marketplace integration)
- `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN`

Session security (recommended in production):
- `SCHEDULING_SESSION_SECRET` ‚Äî long random string for cookie encryption

Calendar email invites when a customer books (2-hour Outlook calendar events):
- `RESEND_API_KEY` ‚Äî from [Resend](https://resend.com)
- `BOOKING_EMAIL_FROM` ‚Äî e.g. `Mobile Dog Salon <bookings@mobiledog-salon.com>` (verified domain)
- `BOOKING_ORGANIZER_EMAIL` ‚Äî organizer on calendar invites (defaults to bookings@)

Customer booking confirmations (email + optional SMS ‚Äî simpler than Go High Level):
- Same `RESEND_API_KEY` sends the customer a confirmation email with calendar attachment
- `TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID` ‚Äî from [Twilio Console](https://console.twilio.com) (starts with `AC...`)
- `TWILIO_API_KEY_SID` + `TWILIO_API_KEY_SECRET` ‚Äî API key credentials (recommended), **or** `TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN`
- `TWILIO_FROM_NUMBER` ‚Äî your Twilio phone number in E.164, e.g. `+17145551234`

SMS is sent only when the customer opts in on the booking form (`smsOptIn`).

Test: `node scripts/test-twilio-connection.mjs`

Twilio inbound SMS webhook (configure in Console ‚Üí Phone Number ‚Üí Messaging):
- Webhook URL: `https://mobiledog-salon.com/api/twilio/inbound` (HTTP POST)
- Handles START, STOP, HELP keywords for A2P compliance

Print A2P registration copy: `node scripts/print-a2p-campaign-info.mjs`

### Appointment reminders (24h + 2h before)

When a customer books, **Upstash QStash** schedules two callbacks to send reminders at the right time. A **daily Vercel Cron** (Hobby plan) runs as a backup sweep for anything missed.

- **Email** to every confirmed booking at **24 hours** and **2 hours** before
- **SMS** at the same times when the customer opted in (`smsOptIn`)

Required:
- Same `RESEND_API_KEY` and Twilio vars as confirmations above
- `CRON_SECRET` ‚Äî Vercel sends `Authorization: Bearer <CRON_SECRET>` to `/api/cron/reminders`
- **Upstash QStash** (same Upstash account as Redis):
  - `QSTASH_TOKEN` ‚Äî from [Upstash Console ‚Üí QStash](https://console.upstash.com/qstash)
  - `QSTASH_CURRENT_SIGNING_KEY` and `QSTASH_NEXT_SIGNING_KEY` ‚Äî QStash signing keys
  - `QSTASH_CALLBACK_URL` ‚Äî `https://mobiledog-salon.com` (production base URL for callbacks)

Manual test:
```bash
node scripts/run-reminders.mjs
# production backup sweep:
SMOKE_BASE_URL=https://mobiledog-salon.com node scripts/run-reminders.mjs
```

Cron backup schedule: daily at 16:00 UTC in `vercel.json`. Per-appointment timing uses QStash.

Optional routing accuracy (not required):
- `GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY` ‚Äî Geocoding API for street-level addresses on groomer routes (optional; ZIP fallbacks still work without it).

### Localhost (production appointment data)

Pull env vars from Vercel into `.env.local` (gitignored):

```bash
vercel env pull .env.local --environment=production
```

Then restart the local server (`npm run 67` or `npm run dev`).

Optional password overrides (plain text, per account):
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_MELANIE` ‚Äî Melanie groomer login (single password; overrides defaults)
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_DIAMOND` ‚Äî Diamond groomer login
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_JESSICA` ‚Äî Jessica groomer login (Chris uses same account)

Optional bcrypt hash overrides (comma-separated for multiple accepted passwords):
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_HASH_MELANIE` ‚Äî overrides Melanie defaults (`Licky`, `licky`, `Licky2026!!`)
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_HASH_DIAMOND` ‚Äî overrides Diamond default hash
- `SCHEDULING_PASSWORD_HASH_JESSICA` ‚Äî overrides Jessica default hash

Jessica trial booking window (customer self-booking):
- `JESSICA_TRIAL_BOOKING_RESTRICTED` ‚Äî set to `0` or `false` to lift the trial cap (default: restricted)
- `JESSICA_BOOKING_HORIZON_DAYS` ‚Äî max days ahead customers can book Jessica (default: `7`)

## Client payment portal (Square)

Client portal: https://mobiledog-salon.com/client/login  
Staff portal: sign in at groomer/admin login ‚Üí **Payments** tab

### Get Square credentials

1. Sign in at [Square Developer Dashboard](https://developer.squareup.com/apps)
2. Open your application (or create one)
3. Copy **Application ID** ‚Üí `SQUARE_APPLICATION_ID`
4. Under Credentials, create/copy **Access token** ‚Üí `SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN`
5. In Square Dashboard ‚Üí Locations, copy your location ID ‚Üí `SQUARE_LOCATION_ID`
6. Set `SQUARE_ENVIRONMENT` to `sandbox` for testing or `production` for live charges

Required for live card processing:
- `SQUARE_ACCESS_TOKEN` ‚Äî Square API access token
- `SQUARE_APPLICATION_ID` ‚Äî Square application ID (Web Payments SDK)
- `SQUARE_LOCATION_ID` ‚Äî Square business location ID
- `SQUARE_ENVIRONMENT` ‚Äî `sandbox` or `production`

Optional:
- `CLIENT_SESSION_SECRET` ‚Äî separate cookie encryption for client accounts

Client accounts stored in `data/clients.json` (or Upstash Redis when configured).

### Licky AI chat (client portal)

Off by default. To enable:
- `LICKY_ENABLED=1` ‚Äî server (chat API)
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_LICKY_ENABLED=1` ‚Äî show the chat widget (set both on Vercel, then redeploy)

Required when Licky is enabled:
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` ‚Äî from [OpenAI API keys](https://platform.openai.com/api-keys)

Optional:
- `OPENAI_MODEL` ‚Äî defaults to `gpt-4o-mini` (fast, cost-effective for support chat)

**Production:** Add `OPENAI_API_KEY` in Vercel ‚Üí Project ‚Üí Environment Variables ‚Üí Production.

Or run (with your key):
```bash
node scripts/connect-licky.mjs sk-your-openai-key
npm run test-licky
```

**Production (required):** Install [Upstash for Redis](https://vercel.com/marketplace/upstash) on your Vercel project.
The integration sets `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL` / `UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN` (or `KV_REST_API_URL` / `KV_REST_API_TOKEN`).
Without Redis, groomer saves fail on production and schedules reset on deploy.

Availability **history** (for admin restore) is stored in the same Redis database.

## Go High Level (confirmation emails + reminders)

When a customer books, the site syncs to Go High Level so you can send **automatic confirmation emails and appointment reminders**.

### 1. API credentials (Vercel env vars)

1. In GHL ‚Üí **Settings** ‚Üí **Business Profile** ‚Üí copy **Location ID** ‚Üí `GHL_LOCATION_ID`
2. GHL ‚Üí **Settings** ‚Üí **Integrations** ‚Üí **Private Integrations** ‚Üí Create key with scopes:
   - `contacts.write`, `contacts.readonly`
   - `calendars.write`, `calendars.readonly`
   - `calendars/events.write`
   - `workflows.write` (if using workflow enrollment)
3. `GHL_API_KEY` ‚Äî the private integration token

Test locally: `node scripts/test-ghl-connection.mjs` (lists your GHL calendars)

### 2. Calendar IDs (triggers GHL appointment emails)

Each booking creates a **GHL calendar appointment** with `toNotify: true`, which fires GHL's built-in confirmation + reminder system.

1. GHL ‚Üí **Calendars** ‚Üí open Melanie's calendar ‚Üí copy calendar ID
2. Repeat for Diamond (or use one shared calendar)

```
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_MELANIE=...
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_DIAMOND=...
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_JESSICA=...
# or a single shared calendar:
GHL_CALENDAR_ID=...
```

Optional: `GHL_USER_ID_MELANIE`, `GHL_USER_ID_DIAMOND` to assign appointments to staff users.

### 3. Confirmation + reminder workflow (recommended)

Create a workflow in GHL ‚Üí **Automation**:

**Option A ‚Äî Customer Booked Appointment trigger** (if using calendar API above)
1. Trigger: **Customer Booked Appointment** ‚Üí filter to your MDS calendar(s)
2. Action: **Send Email** ‚Äî booking confirmation template
3. Action: **Wait** ‚Üí until 24 hours before appointment
4. Action: **Send Email** or **Send SMS** ‚Äî reminder
5. Action: **Wait** ‚Üí until 2 hours before appointment
6. Action: **Send SMS** ‚Äî day-of reminder (filter: tag `sms-opt-in`)

**Option B ‚Äî Inbound Webhook trigger** (works without calendar IDs)
1. Trigger: **Inbound Webhook** ‚Üí copy URL ‚Üí `GHL_WEBHOOK_URL`
2. Map webhook fields (`firstName`, `email`, `appointmentDate`, `appointmentTime`, `petName`, `groomer`, etc.)
3. Same email + wait + reminder actions as above

**Option C ‚Äî Add to existing workflow via API**
1. Copy workflow ID from GHL workflow URL ‚Üí `GHL_BOOKING_WORKFLOW_ID`
2. Each booking enrolls the contact into that workflow automatically

### 4. Custom contact fields (optional, for email merge tags)

Create these custom fields in GHL ‚Üí **Settings** ‚Üí **Custom Fields** (Contact):

`pet_name`, `pet_breed`, `pet_size`, `service`, `service_price`, `groomer`, `appointment_date`, `appointment_time`, `appointment_address`, `booking_id`, `booking_notes`

The booking API upserts these on every contact automatically.

### 5. Add all vars to Vercel

Project ‚Üí **mobile-dog-salon** ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables ‚Üí Production:

```
GHL_API_KEY=
GHL_LOCATION_ID=
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_MELANIE=
GHL_CALENDAR_ID_DIAMOND=
GHL_BOOKING_WORKFLOW_ID=   (optional)
GHL_WEBHOOK_URL=           (optional)
```

## Local development
Data is stored in `data/scheduling.json` and `data/clients.json` without Redis.
Keep `data/scheduling.json` availability empty in git ‚Äî groomers set hours via the dashboard.

**Match production availability locally:** Add the same Upstash/Vercel KV vars to `.env.local` so local dev reads the live Redis database:

```
KV_REST_API_URL=
KV_REST_API_TOKEN=
```

Run `vercel env pull .env.local --environment=production` from the project root, or copy these from Vercel ‚Üí Project ‚Üí Settings ‚Üí Environment Variables. Without Redis locally, the booking calendar will be empty even though production has groomer hours.
